## Description

This blueprint provides support for running custom actions whenever any of the buttons or dial gestures are used on the Philips Hue Tap dial switch (models 8719514440937 / 8719514440999). It targets controllers integrated via Zigbee2MQTT and normalises the rich event set exposed by the device—short and long presses for each of the four buttons plus directional dial events (step, slow rotate, fast rotate) and the computed brightness step events.

Each action emitted by the remote is translated into a semantic controller action (such as `button_1_short`, `dial_rotate_right_repeat`, `dial_brightness_step_up`) that can be consumed directly by Hooks or custom action sequences. Long press inputs optionally loop until a matching release event is received, mirroring the behaviour of other Awesome HA Blueprints controllers.

:::tip
Automations created with this blueprint can be connected with one or more [Hooks](/docs/blueprints/hooks) supported by this controller. Hooks allow you to quickly build controller-based automations for lights, media players, covers and more. See the list of [Hooks available for this controller](#available-hooks) for additional details.
:::

