## Available Hooks

### Light

This Hook blueprint allows you to control a light including brightness and colour adjustments using the Tap dial’s buttons and dial gestures.

#### Default Mapping

- Button 1 short press -> Toggle
- Button 2 short press -> Color up
- Button 2 long press -> Color up (continuous, until release)
- Button 3 short press -> Color down
- Button 3 long press -> Color down (continuous, until release)
- Button 4 short press -> Turn off
- Dial rotate right step -> Brightness up
- Dial rotate right slow/fast -> Brightness up (continuous, until release)
- Dial rotate left step -> Brightness down
- Dial rotate left slow/fast -> Brightness down (continuous, until release)

[Light Hook docs](/docs/blueprints/hooks/light)

## Additional Notes

- The dial can emit both “step” rotations and continuous rotations (`slow` / `fast`) as well as calculated brightness step events. The blueprint exposes each of these so Hooks can distinguish between discrete adjustments and continuous ramps.
- Releases for long button presses are surfaced as their own actions, allowing Hooks or custom sequences to stop loops or handle clean-up when the button is released.

